+ Edit CHANGELOG.md (use git log to get the history)

+ Sync everything to GitHub

+ Create and push a new tag (instructions from https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Basics-Tagging):
    git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "vX.Y.Z"
    git push origin vX.Y.Z

+ Edit the release notes on github

+ Build picachooser

    python setup.py install

+ Build and sync the dist files to pypi

    python -m build
    python -m twine upload --repository picachooser_test dist/* --verbose

+ Rebuild Docker container and push

    builddocker.sh
    testdocker.sh

